# Static site (agent)

- This is HTML5 static website
- No external dependencies.
- Markup should be minimalistic, use pure tags like <b>, <ul>, <p>, <h1>, etc. when possible
- Images live under `images/`
- CSS is `main.css`
- CSS should use styles (.x), not ids (#x)
- PDFs live under `dl/`
- Website should be adaptive, min supported width is 320px
- Every page should have breadcrumbs in a style 'Home /' or 'Home / Topics /'. Current page title is NOT added in the breadcrumbs - it's already there in <h1> below. 'Sessions' are not added into breadcrumbs.
- Every page has contents menu with top-level links. Some top-level links are aggregated under 'Sessions' category, but they should still be considered as top-level. The current page’s entry in Contents must be plain bold text (`<b>…</b>`), never a link to the same URL. On a topic detail page under `topics/`, **Topics** in Contents is `<a href="../topics.html"><b>Topics</b></a>` (link + bold); individual topic pages are **not** listed in the global Contents menu (only on `topics.html`).

When working on content (not on global markup by explicit request):
- Minimal additions and changes to CSS are allowed, for huge ones request confirmation